      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOVEMETO NZ (9) continued a strong run of form when he raced parked but proved too good by 7 metres here a fortnight ago, giving him two wins and two placings from his last four starts. Draws on the back row this time but came from this barrier when scoring easily here last month. Take beating. REMUS PHOENIX (5) was runner-up to Lovemeto last time but got the better of him when scoring by a neck two back at this circuit and distance. With that rival drawn on the back row tonight he is a chance to beat him again. IM BOBBY (8) led and faded when resuming but he is much better than that and generally improves into his campaigns having yet to salute when fresh but won twice when second-up. Draws for a trail so looking for better. PINNIE (1) has a decent record at this shorter distance and draws to be competitive and does ALDEBARAN ACRUX (2) who has been solid at her last couple including a Group 1 placing in Sydney.",
